1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,399
Here is a number worth knowing.

2
00:00:02,399 --> 00:00:10,000
According to Statistics Canada, more than 27 percent of Canadians aged 15 and older have at least one disability.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:12,800
In Ontario, that number is even higher.

4
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:20,800
That means more than one in four people who come to UHN for care may experience barriers related to disability.

5
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:28,000
And many disabilities are non-visible — you may not know someone has a disability unless they tell you.

6
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:33,200
The reality is that healthcare systems were often designed without disability in mind.

7
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:44,800
Narrow doorways, small print on intake forms, appointment booking systems that require phone calls, waiting rooms with no seating options — these are everyday barriers that affect real people.

8
00:00:44,800 --> 00:00:50,000
When we remove these barriers, we do not just help people with disabilities.

9
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:58,800
We create a better experience for everyone — older adults, people recovering from surgery, caregivers with strollers, anyone navigating a stressful moment.

10
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:00,800
Accessibility benefits all of us.

11
00:01:00,800 --> 00:01:02,800
And it starts with understanding.
